-- Albaraka Banking Sees Acquisition in Indonesia in First Quarter, CEO Says
-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 2010-10-31T08:02:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-31/albaraka-banking-sees-acquisition-in-indonesia-in-first-quarter-ceo-says.html
Albaraka Banking Group has
identified targets for acquisition in Indonesia and expects to
complete a purchase there in the first quarter of 2011, Chief
Executive Officer Adnan Yousif said.  The group has also identified targets for acquisitions in
Malaysia, Yousif said in an interview today at an economic
conference in Kuwait.  The group expects its assets in 2010 to be at $15 billion,
while net income is expected to be better than 2009, he said,
without giving specific details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
